Fixed cost models are used to figure out whether or not to produce something and how much.In the Jenniffer & Co. problem I attempted to figure out whethere it was more effective to do 10 haircuts in a day or 5 colors by inputing the fixed costs for each. This is important to do because otherwise , if I do not set my prices correctly I could be loosing money, or if I offer a serive that isn't maximizing my daily profit I could be loosing money.

Set covering models are used to figure out how to serve the needs of a certain area the best way possible. An example of a set covering model is when we figured out how many fire departments were needed to cover a certain area. This is important because it is necessary to know the best way to take care of a certain area, especially for safety reasons such as fire departments hospitals, etc. in order to keep everyone within an area happy and healthy.
